❓ Write a stored function to print sum of income of person living in “ ” area type. (Accept area type as input parameter). Display appropriate message for invalid area type.


---

✅ Function

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION sum_income(a_type VARCHAR)
RETURNS NUMERIC AS
$$
DECLARE
    total NUMERIC;
BEGIN
    IF a_type NOT IN ('urban','rural') THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Invalid area type';
    END IF;

    SELECT SUM(income) INTO total
    FROM person p
    JOIN area a ON p.aname = a.aname
    WHERE a.area_type = a_type;

    RETURN total;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;


---

✅ Call

SELECT sum_income('urban');


