❓ Write a procedure to accept two numbers from user and display division of two numbers. Use raise to display error messages for division by zero error. [5 marks]


---

✅ Procedure

CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE divide_nums(a INT, b INT)
LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $$
BEGIN
    IF b = 0 THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Division by zero not allowed';
    END IF;

    RAISE NOTICE 'Division = %', a / b;
END;
$$;


---

✅ Call

CALL divide_nums(10, 2);
